<h3 class="topic">The Machine</h3>
<p>
  All printing is done on a Risograph MZ990 Digital Duplicator.
</p>

<p>
  Like a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mimeograph">mimeograph</a>,
  the Risograph works by transferring an image
  (either from a digital file or from the glass top) to a thin stencil
  called a "master." The master is then wrapped around a single color drum
  filled with liquid ink. The ink is pushed through the master and on to the
  paper (which runs flat through machine) while the drum rotates at high speed.
  It looks a lot like this
  <a href="http://25.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lp9h6cRUMw1qzjd4oo1_500.gif">animated .gif</a>.
</p>

